div.h2: Free Grab 'n Go meals are available Monday through Friday at the Brownsville Middle School kitchen entrance or Fort Burd Church from 11:30 to 12:30. Friday pickup includes meals for the weekend. You MUST call 724-785-2155 extension 2507 by 9:30 a.m. each day that you need meals.

em.u: Kindergarten students for the 2020 - 2021 school year

span.span: Due to the closure of schools delaying Kindergarten Registration, we are reaching out to begin planning for the fall. We are asking all of those who intend to register a child for kindergarten for the first time in the Brownsville Area School District to complete the short form linked below.Â
This is not a formal registration; however, it helps us to begin the process for those children. Formal registration will tentatively take place in July 2020 -- actual date TBA.
This is for incoming KINDERGARTEN students for the 2020 - 2021 school year only. Thank you.

Our two primary goals are: 1) to preserve the safety and health of our students and staff, and 2) to keep K-12 students engaged in commensurately challenging learning activities during the extended school closure. It is a top priority of ours to ensure continuity in learning for all of our students using the best means we have available for teaching and learning exchanges.Â
